questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot microservice under heavy load starts throwing `OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space` after several days. Analysis of a heap dump reveals that thousands of `byte[]` arrays are being held by `ThreadLocal` variables within the `ThreadPoolExecutor` used by the `@Async` processing layer. The following code is identified as the culprit:

java
@Service
public class DataProcessor {
    private static final ThreadLocal<byte[]> contextBuffer = new ThreadLocal<>();

    @Transactional
    public void process(Payload data) {
        byte[] buffer = transform(data);
        contextBuffer.set(buffer);
        saveToDatabase(data);
        // Business logic continues...
    }

    private byte[] transform(Payload data) { /* returns 1MB array */ return new byte[1024 * 1024]; }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Data JPA application slows down significantly when processing a large batch of 50,000 records within a single `@Transactional` method. Even though the JVM heap is large, the application spends 80% of its time in 'GC overhead' and eventually crashes. The code looks like this:

java
@Transactional
public void bulkUpdate(List<Long> ids) {
    for (Long id : ids) {
        UserEntity user = repository.findById(id).get();
        user.setStatus("PROCESSED");
        repository.save(user);
    }
}
